---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/globals.css";
import { Header } from "../../components/Header";
import InnerPageCTA from "../../components/InnerPageCTA.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const b = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title="UK Consumers Report Worse Delivery Experience Than US and Europeans Despite Global Supply Chain Crisis - parcelLab"
  description="parcelLab research reveals UK consumers face significantly worse delivery experiences than counterparts in the US, France, and Germany."
>
  <Header client:load />
  <main>
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section class="section-generous">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1440px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px]">
          <a href={`${b}/blog/`} class="group mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--ink-muted)] transition-colors hover:text-[#3D3AD3]">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="transition-transform group-hover:-translate-x-0.5"><path d="M19 12H5"/><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
            Back to blog
          </a>
          <span class="mb-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-[#3D3AD3]">Research</span>
          <h1 class="text-display text-[var(--ink)]">UK Consumers Report Worse Delivery Experience Than US and Europeans Despite Global Supply Chain Crisis</h1>
          <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">
            <span>By <strong class="font-medium text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">parcelLab Team</strong></span>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <time datetime="2021-12-17">December 17, 2021</time>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <span>5 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Body -->
    <section class="pb-16 md:pb-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-lg">
          As the Office for Budget Responsibility reported on supply chain bottlenecks exacerbated by Brexit, parcelLab research revealed concerning disparities in delivery experiences across markets. A YouGov omnibus survey of 2,000+ consumers per country uncovered that UK shoppers face significantly worse outcomes than their international counterparts.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Failed Deliveries</h2>
        <div class="my-10 rounded-2xl bg-[var(--surface-sunken)] p-8">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-[var(--ink-muted)]">Key Finding</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-lg font-medium text-[var(--ink)]">Nearly two-fifths (39%) of UK consumers reported orders that never arrived, compared to 18% in the US, 22% in France, and 23% in Germany.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Delivery Delays</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Over 41% of UK online shoppers experienced packages not arriving when needed, versus 23% in France, 27% in Germany, and 29% in the US. The gap between UK and other markets is striking.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Brand Loyalty Impact</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          The consequences of poor delivery extend beyond individual transactions. When experiencing poor delivery:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#F4373D" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="15" y1="9" x2="9" y2="15"/><line x1="9" y1="9" x2="15" y2="15"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">35% of UK consumers</strong> refused to reorder from that retailer</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#F4373D" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="15" y1="9" x2="9" y2="15"/><line x1="9" y1="9" x2="15" y2="15"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">Significantly higher</strong> than France (21%), the US (23%), and Germany (25%)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#F4373D" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="15" y1="9" x2="9" y2="15"/><line x1="9" y1="9" x2="15" y2="15"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">49% of UK consumers</strong> with negative experiences contacted customer services to locate packages</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">What UK Consumers Demand</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          UK shoppers have clear expectations for enhanced communication:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">61%</strong> wanted shipment notifications</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">66%</strong> requested regular package location updates</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">47%</strong> desired map-based tracking</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]"><strong class="text-[var(--ink)]">65%</strong> expected immediate alerts regarding delays</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Research Methodology</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          YouGov omnibus survey of 2,000 representative consumers per country: UK (2,076), Germany (2,184), France (2,048), US (1,163) adults. Fieldwork was conducted during the October-August 2021 period, weighted to represent all adults aged 18+.
        </p>

        <div class="my-12 border-t border-[var(--line)]"></div>

        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          The data paints a clear picture: UK consumers are experiencing worse delivery outcomes than their international counterparts, and they are more likely to abandon retailers as a result. Proactive, branded post-purchase communication is no longer a nice-to-have -- it's essential for customer retention.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <InnerPageCTA />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
